<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="247" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[491,1529,229,2015]" pageId="5" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[531,778,1646,1670]" pageId="5" pageNumber="247">Differential diagnosis</emphasis>
— The new species was compared with 18 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Keifer" authorityYear="1944" box="[1229,1304,1645,1669]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="5" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1229,1304,1645,1669]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="247">Aceria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species associated with the plants of family 
<taxonomicName box="[764,879,1680,1704]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="5" pageNumber="247" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Solanaceae</taxonomicName>
known to date. The new species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Nalepa)" baseAuthorityName="Nalepa" baseAuthorityYear="1892" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="5" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eucricotes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="247">Aceria eucricotes</emphasis>
(Nalepa)
</taxonomicName>
collected on 
<taxonomicName box="[841,1048,1716,1739]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="5" pageNumber="247" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="europaeum">
<emphasis box="[841,1048,1716,1739]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="247">Lycium europaeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. from 
<collectingCountry box="[1137,1228,1715,1739]" name="Algeria" pageId="5" pageNumber="247">Algeria</collectingCountry>
and, previously, also on 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="5" pageNumber="247" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruthenicum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="247">L. ruthenicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[677,715,1750,1773]" name="Iran" pageId="5" pageNumber="247">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lotfollahi P. &amp; de Lillo E. &amp; Haddad Irani-Nejad K." box="[730,970,1749,1773]" pageId="5" pageNumber="247" pagination="1167 - 1180" refId="ref7053" refString="Lotfollahi P., de Lillo E., Haddad Irani-Nejad K. 2017. Contribution on Aceria spp. (Acari: Trombidiformes: Eriophyoidea) from southwest of East Azerbaijan province in Iran: new records and description of two new species. Syst. Appl. Acar., 22 (8): 1167 - 1180. doi: 10.11158 / saa. 22.8.4" type="journal article" year="2017">
Lotfollahi 
<emphasis box="[849,906,1749,1773]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="247">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). Both species have completely smooth prodorsal shields, similar number of empodial rays and body setal length. But these two species differ in number of dorsal semiannuli (
<quantity box="[802,880,1818,1842]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1684" metricValueMax="1.3462" metricValueMin="0.9906" pageId="5" pageNumber="247" unit="in" value="46.0" valueMax="53.0" valueMin="39.0">39–53 in</quantity>
the new species 
<emphasis box="[1082,1150,1819,1842]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="247">versus</emphasis>
<quantity box="[1156,1242,1818,1842]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5748" metricValueMax="1.8542" metricValueMin="1.2953999999999999" pageId="5" pageNumber="247" unit="in" value="62.0" valueMax="73.0" valueMin="51.0">51–73 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nalepa" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1256,1394,1818,1842]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="5" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eucricotes">
<emphasis box="[1256,1394,1818,1842]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="247">A. eucricotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), number of semiannuli between coxae and genital coverflap (
<quantity box="[1049,1108,1853,1877]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" metricValueMax="2.032" metricValueMin="1.524" pageId="5" pageNumber="247" unit="in" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">6–8 in</quantity>
the new species 
<emphasis box="[1308,1376,1854,1877]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="247">versus</emphasis>
<quantity box="[1384,1443,1853,1877]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" metricValueMax="1.27" metricValueMin="0.762" pageId="5" pageNumber="247" unit="in" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nalepa" baseAuthorityYear="1892" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="5" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eucricotes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="247">A. eucricotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). In addition, 
<taxonomicName authority="Tajaddod &amp; Lotfollahi &amp; Lillo, 2020" authorityName="Tajaddod &amp; Lotfollahi &amp; Lillo" authorityYear="2020" box="[756,941,1887,1911]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="5" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ajabshiriensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[756,941,1887,1911]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="247">A. ajabshiriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[941,1001,1888,1912]" pageId="5" pageNumber="247">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[941,1001,1888,1912]" pageId="5" pageNumber="247" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a short flexible distally acuminate frontal lobe, while 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nalepa" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[614,752,1922,1946]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="5" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eucricotes">
<emphasis box="[614,752,1922,1946]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="247">A. eucricotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
doesn’t have a frontal lobe. Finally, the female genital coverflap of the new species is ornamented with 9–10 longitudinal striae, whereas 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nalepa" baseAuthorityYear="1892" box="[1201,1340,1956,1980]" class="Arachnida" family="Eriophyidae" genus="Aceria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Prostigmata" pageId="5" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eucricotes">
<emphasis box="[1201,1340,1956,1980]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="247">A. eucricotes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a smooth coverflap.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="248" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[491,1490,229,288]" pageId="6" pageNumber="248">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[531,642,230,254]" pageId="6" pageNumber="248">Remarks</emphasis>
— This is the third eriophyoid species collected on 
<taxonomicName box="[1196,1346,229,253]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Lycium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="6" pageNumber="248" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ruthenicum">
<emphasis box="[1196,1346,229,253]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="248">L. ruthenicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and all three species were collected from this host plant in 
<collectingCountry box="[983,1021,265,288]" name="Iran" pageId="6" pageNumber="248">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lotfollahi, P. &amp; de Lillo, E. &amp; Haddad Irani-Nejad, K." box="[1035,1262,264,288]" pageId="6" pageNumber="248" pagination="17 - 27" refId="ref7121" refString="Lotfollahi, P., de Lillo, E., Haddad Irani-Nejad, K. 2014. Three new species from the subfamily Phyllocoptinae (Acari, Trombidiformes, Eriophyidae) in Iran. ZooKeys, 426: 17 - 27. doi: 10.3897 / zookeys. 426.8087" type="journal article" year="2014">
Lotfollahi 
<emphasis box="[1148,1195,264,288]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="248">et al</emphasis>
. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lotfollahi P. &amp; de Lillo E. &amp; Haddad Irani-Nejad K." box="[1272,1331,264,288]" pageId="6" pageNumber="248" pagination="1167 - 1180" refId="ref7053" refString="Lotfollahi P., de Lillo E., Haddad Irani-Nejad K. 2017. Contribution on Aceria spp. (Acari: Trombidiformes: Eriophyoidea) from southwest of East Azerbaijan province in Iran: new records and description of two new species. Syst. Appl. Acar., 22 (8): 1167 - 1180. doi: 10.11158 / saa. 22.8.4" type="journal article" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
